news.title: Over 450 infrastructural projects hit by cost overrun in May 2024
news.para: In May this year, 458 infrastructure projects in India, each with an investment of Rs 150 crore or more, experienced a cost overrun totaling more than Rs 5.71 lakh crore, according to an official report.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh CM directs reduction in stamp duty for rent agreements
news.para: He emphasized that an online system for stamps and registration is crucial for ease of living and better record and data management. Preparations should be made regarding this as soon as possible and a draft should be readied and presented.

news.title: Chandigarh civic body seeks release of Rs 32 crore for land acquired 15-20 years back
news.para: For the last 15 to 20 years, all this amount has been lying unused with the reference courts because of legal issues surrounding the compensation awarded and land ownership.

news.title: Ghaziabad civic body yet to collect Rs 19 crore property tax from defaulters
news.para: According to the corporation, it had 2,900 property tax defaulters across its five zones in the 2023-24 fiscal, which ended on March 31 this year.

news.title: Goa's town planning department revises fee structure to convert land
news.para: The conversion of a plot will cost Rs 1,000 per sqm if the size is more than 500sqm, a flat processing fee of Rs 10,000 will also be charged, said chief town planner (land use) Ranjit Borkar.

news.title: Existing home sales in USA fall 0.7% in May 2024
news.para: There was, however, some encouraging news on the housing market, with the National Association of Realtors reporting on Friday that housing inventory jumped last month to the highest level in nearly two years.

news.title: Ahmedabad civic body sells four commercial plots for Rs 60 crore
news.para: Interestingly, a commercial plot in Isanpur sold for a higher rate than a commercial plot in Motera. The Motera plot went for a total of Rs 9.73 crore at the rate of Rs 1.01 lakh per sq m, against its base price of Rs 1 lakh per sq m.

news.title: Illegal structures in government land: Telangana HC asks collector to respond
news.para: Gadeela Raghuveer Reddy of Kondapaka in Siddipet filed a PIL, alleging that the authorities not only entered the names of the encroachers in revenue records, but also granted the layout plan, building permission, etc., in survey number 166 in Medchal district.

news.title: Bengaluru: FIR registered against Provident Apartment for dumping wastewater on road
news.para: Thalaghattapura Police, along with BBMP engineers, inspected the site known for the leakage of untreated water from the apartment complex onto the road.

news.title: Unity Small Finance Bank inks pact to acquire office space worth Rs 393 crore
news.para: The developer of the Santacruz project received a letter of intimation (LOI) and approval from the Slum Rehabilitation Authority for the project in August 2023.

news.title: Noida authority extends rehabilitation offer to builders with projects under insolvency
news.para: Govt’s rehabilitation package, introduced last Dec, gives several concessions to developers, including a two-year waiver from paying interests and penalties imposed during the pandemic.

news.title: Sebi disposes of proceedings against former Unitech promoters
news.para: It also alleged that Ajay Chandra was a non-executive director in UCP, while Unitech had a 4.52 per cent stake in UCP through its subsidiary Nectrus Ltd -- a foreign subsidiary of Unitech whose account was held with UBS Singapore Branch.

news.title: Prestige Estates to raise $598.6 million
news.para: The Indian real estate developer added its board has approved the monetization of its hospitality assets through a share issue and has formed a sub-committee to oversee the process.

news.title: Residential property prices in Germany fall by 5.7% in Q1 2024
news.para: High financing and construction costs continue to weigh on Europe's biggest economy, triggering the most severe property crisis in the country in decades.

news.title: Walplast Products invests Rs 300 crore in capacity expansion
news.para: These new plants located in Gujarat, Maharashtra, Madhya Pradesh and Andhra Pradesh will enhance Walplast's capacities for White, Grey and Gypsum products by 8,00,000 metric tons (MT) annually.

news.title: Kerala government to withdraw notification for acquiring land for Sabarimala airport
news.para: ​​​The government has also told the court that it will conduct a fresh Social Impact Assessment (SIA) study with regard to the project through a different agency.

news.title: Madras HC restrains Tamil Nadu government from evicting SRM Hotel
news.para: Justice G R Swaminathan, slamming officials for barging into the property on June 14 and taking possession of the property, the 30-year lease period for which had lapsed.

news.title: Telangana government exploring possibilities for the expansion of Hyderabad
news.para: Chief minister A Revanth Reddy in March had asked the municipal administration department to work out the expansion plans of the city civic body in view of rapid development in Greater Hyderabad.
